        <h2>About Mads Mikkelsen</h2>
        <p>
            Mads Mikkelsen (born 1965) is a Danish actor known for his versatile roles in film and television.
            He rose to international fame through performances in <em>Casino Royale</em>, <em>Doctor Strange</em>, and the acclaimed series <em>Hannibal</em>.
            With a career spanning decades, he is celebrated for his intense and charismatic screen presence.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="career">
        <h2>Life & Career</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Born in Copenhagen, Denmark in 1965</li>
            <li>Started his career as a gymnast and dancer before moving into acting</li>
            <li>Gained recognition with the Danish film <em>Pusher</em> (1996)</li>
            <li>Won Best Actor at the Cannes Film Festival in 2012 for <em>The Hunt</em></li>
            <li>Starred in major franchises including James Bond, Marvel, and Star Wars</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section class="contributions">
        <h2>Key Contributions</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Memorable villain Le Chiffre in <em>Casino Royale</em></li>
            <li>Acclaimed performance as Dr. Hannibal Lecter in <em>Hannibal</em> TV series</li>
            <li>Praise for roles in Danish cinema, including <em>The Hunt</em> and <em>Another Round</em></li>
            <li>Recognized as one of Denmark’s most successful international actors</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

